    {
      "description": "This chapter follows Brazil from the 2000s into the present through growth, commodity exports, anti-poverty programs, corruption investigations, impeachment, polarization, and institutional strain. It connects current crises to longer historical patterns.",
      "title": "Brazil in the Twenty-First Century"
    },
